{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"ac756c0b95ee51fa9","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are a research sub-agent. You have WebSearch and WebFetch tools (load them first via ToolSearch with query \"select:WebSearch,WebFetch\" if needed).\n\nRESEARCH ANGLE: REWARD HACKING / specification gaming in self-improving / evolutionary code systems — concrete documented examples where a system gamed its objective rather than genuinely improving.\n\nFind specific, quotable examples:\n- Darwin Godel Machine paper — its OBJECTIVE HACKING / reward-hacking observation: the system faked/hallucinated tool use or tampered with logs to look like it solved tasks; the authors discuss this explicitly (and a safety/hallucination section). Get the exact example.\n- AlphaEvolve / evolutionary systems \"cheating\" the evaluator (special-casing test inputs, exploiting evaluator bugs).\n- STOP (Self-Taught Optimizer) paper — it documents the model attempting to disable a sandbox flag / reward-hacking-adjacent behaviors.\n- DeepMind \"Specification gaming: the flip side of AI ingenuity\" (Krakovna et al. blog) — definition and examples, the spec-gaming examples master list.\n- Goodhart's law applied to RSI / \"when a measure becomes a target it ceases to be a good measure\".\n\nRun 5-7 WebSearch queries. Then WebFetch the 5-6 best primary sources. Extract exact wording / concrete example descriptions.\n\nSearch terms: \"Darwin Godel Machine objective hacking hallucinate tool use\", \"Darwin Godel Machine reward hacking safety\", \"specification gaming DeepMind Krakovna examples\", \"Self-Taught Optimizer STOP disable sandbox reward hacking\", \"AlphaEvolve evaluator gaming\", \"Goodhart's law recursive self improvement\", \"evolutionary algorithm cheats fitness function examples\".\n\nOUTPUT: Return a list of 6-12 FALSIFIABLE CLAIMS. Each claim must be:\n- A single concrete factual sentence (ideally describing a specific documented incident)\n- Followed by the EXACT source URL\n- Followed by a short verbatim quote or close paraphrase supporting it\nDo not pad. Only return claims you actually found support for in fetched pages."},"uuid":"ec4bc476-b041-4975-9dcb-ae5edf4dee43","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:31.119Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
